text.tspan: What mobile OS do you use?
On mobile, Android is king. After 2 obvious ones Ubuntu Touch came in at #4 which was a nice surprise, and then after the unfortunate
dumb phone and blackberry users there's just a lovely mix of the weird and the quirky.
We also have quite a few people, especially
on Android, who have another OS installed
For the OS we had Debian (15), Arch (11), Ubuntu (5), Kali,
For the interface we had None (16), XFCE (6), LXDE (5),
bspwm, fluxbox, GNOME 2, i3, MATE, awesome, and qemu (1).
